title: Mysterious spiral over Alaska probably a result of SpaceX launch
description: Researchers say the event was probably caused by excess fuel released during the launch.

title: Despite bankruptcy, Virgin Orbit CEO says company will launch again
description: After filing for Chapter 11, the company founded by Richard Branson is looking for a suitor to rescue it.

title: Snapchat isn’t known for minting internet stars. It’s trying to change that.
description: Snapchat has been faced with a declining stock price and slow user growth.

title: Google’s AI dilemma: Move fast or ‘don’t be evil’
description: The AI goldrush has put Google's search dominance in jeopardy, and its "don't be evil" credo under pressure.

title: A retired satellite is plummeting to Earth. But don’t panic, NASA says.
description: NASA expects the 660-pound RHESSI satellite, which once observed the sun, to plunge through the atmosphere on Wednesday night and fall to Earth.

title: Inside the secret list of websites that make AI chatbots sound smart
description: An analysis of a chatbot data set by The Washington Post reveals the proprietary, personal, and often offensive websites that go into an AI’s training data.

title: Amazon HQ2 was thought up pre-pandemic. But the world is hybrid now.
description: A sluggish return to the office is dimming some of Amazon's expected boost to Virginia – and prompting some questions about the whole project's future.

title: Have you used Facebook in the past 16 years? You may qualify for payment.
description: Facebook users in the United States can file for compensation as part of a $725 million data privacy settlement.
